  <description type="morphology">Stems decumbent or spreading, 0.1–1.8 dm. Leaf blades: margins entire or shallowly
        dentate. Vertical seeds 0.8–1(–1.2) mm diam.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Fruiting fall.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Alkali flats, brackish beaches, bare bottomlands, lake shores, dried-up pools, somewhat akaline clay flats;</description>
  <description type="elevation">10-1500 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Alta., B.C., N.B., N.S., Sask., Yukon; Alaska, Calif., Colo., Idaho, Maine, Mass., Minn., Mont., Nebr., Nev., N.Mex., N.Y., N.Dak., Oreg., Utah, Wash., Wyo.</description>
